{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"deep-water soloing (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that several climbers have drowned while <b><a href=\"/wiki/Deep-water_soloing\" title=\"Deep-water soloing\">deep-water soloing</a></b> <i>(example pictured)</i>, even though it is safer than <a href=\"/wiki/Free_solo_climbing\" title=\"Free solo climbing\">free solo climbing</a>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deep-water_soloing","retrieved":1773597117343},{"title":"John Allen Chau (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/John_Allen_Chau\" title=\"John Allen Chau\">John Allen Chau</a></b> illegally travelled to <a href=\"/wiki/North_Sentinel_Island\" title=\"North Sentinel Island\">North Sentinel Island</a> in an attempt to convert its inhabitants to Christianity?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Allen_Chau","retrieved":1773597117344},{"title":"Martin-Smith School of Music (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/Martin-Smith_School_of_Music\" title=\"Martin-Smith School of Music\">Martin-Smith School of Music</a></b>, according to one historian, was \"one of the most important black musical institutions\" in the United States?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin-Smith_School_of_Music","retrieved":1773597117347},{"title":"Luca Gargano (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Luca_Gargano\" title=\"Luca Gargano\">Luca Gargano</a></b> discovered thousands of barrels of aged rum in an abandoned Trinidadian distillery, sparking \"Caroni mania\"?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luca_Gargano","retrieved":1773597117349},{"title":"a 1980 Doctor Who serial (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Full_Circle_(Doctor_Who)\" title=\"Full Circle (Doctor Who)\">a 1980 <i>Doctor Who</i> serial</a></b> was written by a seventeen-year-old fan of the show?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Full_Circle_(Doctor_Who)","retrieved":1773597117352},{"title":"Annie Stainer (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Annie_Stainer\" title=\"Annie Stainer\">Annie Stainer</a></b> \"would appear to fly, by delicately and continuously undulating her arms as if they were remarkable wings\" during her solo shows?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Annie_Stainer","retrieved":1773597117353},{"title":"Tomodachi Collection (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <a href=\"/wiki/Shigeru_Miyamoto\" title=\"Shigeru Miyamoto\">Shigeru Miyamoto</a> told his coworkers \"you guys are useless\" after he received a prototype of <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Tomodachi_Collection\" title=\"Tomodachi Collection\">Tomodachi Collection</a></b></i><span class=\"nowrap\" style=\"padding-left:0.1em;\">'s</span> character-creation system?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tomodachi_Collection","retrieved":1773597117355},{"title":"Eric Slover (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Eric_Slover\" title=\"Eric Slover\">Eric Slover</a></b><span class=\"nowrap\">'s</span> wife blessed his dog tags with holy water before <a href=\"/wiki/2026_United_States_intervention_in_Venezuela\" title=\"2026 United States intervention in Venezuela\">Operation Absolute Resolve</a>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eric_Slover","retrieved":1773597117360},{"title":"A Place with the Pigs (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/A_Place_with_the_Pigs\" title=\"A Place with the Pigs\">A Place with the Pigs</a></b></i> was based on a real-life World War&nbsp;II deserter who hid in a pigsty until 1985?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A_Place_with_the_Pigs","retrieved":1773597117362},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r4523569\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transclusion\" about=\"#mwt7\" data-